quote_first: His own case was more desperate and required a desperate expedient–to board the
quote_last: train without buying a ticket. He went on until he reached the edge of the brewery district where he stopped in a small tobacconist’s to buy pipe tobacco and ask questions.
title: The Golden Bough
author: George Gibbs
